central control, but Black's bishop pair offset this.} 10. O-O {The main move, 
which has been played around 250 times.} cxd4 11. Nxd4 Bd7 12. Qb3 {[%csl 
Rb4,Rb7]} Nc6 {Developing and exchanging pieces.} 13. Nxc6 {[%csl Rb4]} Bxc3 {We 
simply vacuum the pieces off the board now and equalise.} 14. Rxc3 Bxc6 15. Bb5 
Bd5 $11 {[%cal Bd5c6,Bc6d5,Bb5c4,Bc4b5] Dozens of games have ended quickly in a 
draw this way. It seems like Black has no theoretical problems in the mainline 
presented here, so White needs to search for deviations earlier to find 
something which can pose some theoretical challenges to the Ragozin with 5. 
Bg5.} *

[Event "Short & Sweet: The Ragozin"]
[Site "The Ragozin"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
